If our people deem it so, you will face a true champion for democracy, the environment, and the unity of our Nation. It will be up to the people to decide who they will entrust their hopes, dreams, and futures to.

To my incumbent opponent, @RepThompson, thank you for your decades of service to our people, but I do not believe you have the right to hold your seat in perpetuity. 

I may not have your experience, but I am absent your entanglements and you are no rival to my passion or heart.
It is up to each of us to take responsibility for the kind of America we want to live in, and it’s up to each of us to show up & vote!

This mid-term Election is significant, and we cannot afford to not show up now; the lives of our children, the civil rights of women and the LGBTQ+ community, and the ravages of unchecked nationalism and misinformation all hang in the balance of what we choose here and now.

Above all else, we’ve proven that it’s possible for any normal American citizen to have the opportunity to compete in the Democratic process, and to everyone who helped to get us to this point, I will always be grateful.
We do not have to agree on policy, but we have to be civil in disagreement and do everything we can to practice love and empathy when we stand for what we believe in.

From the beginning, this campaign aimed to fight back against the divides that have been given life in this country, and it is my belief that our work has helped to start a dialogue to bridge these gaps.

My campaign is not without milestones, as we set a record for face-value signatures with the Sonoma County Registrar of Voters and organized the first Congressional debate in our District in over a decade.
Regardless of the outcome of this Primary, I’m proud to have shot my shot and put myself out there as a new voice in service to our people.

2 years, 2,000+ doors knocked, 1,024 community signatures, many miles on foot and in the car, and the unwavering support of my friends, family, and community have led me to this moment. https://t.co/CJadWCqFdG

If you are currently a registered voter in California’s 5th District (encompassing parts of Sonoma, Solano, Lake, Napa, and Contra Costa counties) please come out and sign my petition to put my name on the ballot for 2022 so I can give our people a new voice in Washington, D.C.

On Saturday December 18th, 2021, I am asking for my community to join me in Santa Rosa’s Courthouse Square at 1:00 PM for the official declaration of my candidacy (I will give a speech and begin collecting the minimum 2,000 registered voter signatures needed to get on the ballot)
Above all else, consider me a friend who wants to see us united in the quest for peace and prosperity for all who would be free.

You can consider me a champion against the existential threats posed by climate change, COVID-19, and authoritarian governments. If you are looking for an advocate for Federal cannabis legalization and criminal justice reform, you can count on me on that front too.
